        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 5:10PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 509 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 9 miles northwest of
Lillington to 7 miles west of Pope AFB to 8 miles southwest of
Raeford to near Laurinburg. Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Sanford, Laurinburg, Raeford, Lillington, Fort Bragg,
Fuquay-Varina, Angier, Maxton, and Pope AFB.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
